    <caseIntroduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>In 2021, Vietnam's electricity production relied predominantly on coal (47% of the power generation) and hydro (31%), contrasting with the 2017 figures of 33% coal and 46% hydro. </p>
<p>During the same period, solar generation in Vietnam went from zero to 33 TWh with installed capacity reaching 16.7 GW. In 2017, wind and solar contributed just 0.2% to the country's electricity, a figure that had risen to 12% by 2021. Feed in Tariff policies payed an important role in this.</p>]]></Value>
    </caseIntroduction>
    <caseLockInBlockList>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "layout": {
    "Umbraco.BlockList": [
      {
        "contentUdi": "umb://element/a05a168b2682472aa3d7bb59c1985902"
      },
      {
        "contentUdi": "umb://element/ee2bf750fc2c456491fb4e3eea972067"
      },
      {
        "contentUdi": "umb://element/cb2e2dfe59364c5a978bafa7147b5eba"
      },
      {
        "contentUdi": "umb://element/afa883745b6d4daab43fd9a75cb00380"
      },
      {
        "contentUdi": "umb://element/1170c94815584d25bae126e4a1a10b95"
      },
      {
        "contentUdi": "umb://element/361dcc12567f456fb39f3faf1b8da337"
      },
      {
        "contentUdi": "umb://element/69b59c793f2a45008dfabbfa7c4ea265"
      }
    ]
  },
  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "5781df7b-a32c-4493-b9fc-90c8e9efebb2",
      "udi": "umb://element/a05a168b2682472aa3d7bb59c1985902",
      "negativePositive": "1",
      "lockInType": [
        "Institutional (and governance)"
      ],
      "bodyText": "<p>Feedback from investors and project developers can accelerate procedures flexibility and administrative streamlining for new energy projects.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "5781df7b-a32c-4493-b9fc-90c8e9efebb2",
      "udi": "umb://element/ee2bf750fc2c456491fb4e3eea972067",
      "negativePositive": "1",
      "lockInType": [
        "Technological (and infrastructural)"
      ],
      "bodyText": "<p>The solar boom experienced by Viet Nam shows domestic policy makers that adequate policies and regional targeting can lead to the rapid deployment of renewable energies, and can help relieve energy shortage in areas dependent on baseload power generation with deteriorating reliability. This is relevant in light of the May/June 2023 droughts and heatwaves that affected the North of the country, where PV penetration is low, led to reduced hydroelectric output, which in turns led to dramatic power outages.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "5781df7b-a32c-4493-b9fc-90c8e9efebb2",
      "udi": "umb://element/cb2e2dfe59364c5a978bafa7147b5eba",
      "negativePositive": "1",
      "lockInType": [
        "Economical"
      ],
      "bodyText": "<p>Mitigating risks in solar projects enabled the establishment of a skilled workforce and a pool of experts who can be readily deployed<br>in upcoming clean energy projects.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "5781df7b-a32c-4493-b9fc-90c8e9efebb2",
      "udi": "umb://element/afa883745b6d4daab43fd9a75cb00380",
      "negativePositive": "0",
      "lockInType": [
        "Technological (and infrastructural)"
      ],
      "bodyText": "<p>Uneven and extensive solar PV deployment caused grid congestion in provinces with sustained high installation rates. The situation was exacerbated as, historically, regions with limited renewable potential received more investment in power distribution and transport infrastructure, mainly to support coal and hydroelectric power facilities. Conversely, areas with abundant renewable potential have lower electricity demand.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "5781df7b-a32c-4493-b9fc-90c8e9efebb2",
      "udi": "umb://element/1170c94815584d25bae126e4a1a10b95",
      "negativePositive": "0",
      "lockInType": [
        "Economical"
      ],
      "bodyText": "<p>Insufficient forecasting for solar PV deployment creates obstacles in achieving medium and long-term power sector goals. Solar PV deployment surpassed its target several years ahead of schedule, resulting in government-issued FiT draft policies being introduced and subsequently revoked, causing uncertainty for project<br>developers.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "5781df7b-a32c-4493-b9fc-90c8e9efebb2",
      "udi": "umb://element/361dcc12567f456fb39f3faf1b8da337",
      "negativePositive": "0",
      "lockInType": [
        "Technological (and infrastructural)"
      ],
      "bodyText": "<p>Ambitious policies focusing on one specific technology can lead to the sudden deployment of a investments and workforce, potentially limiting the availability of funds and skilled professionals for other essential domains requiring adjacent expertise and similar cash inflows, for example grid infrastructure development.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "5781df7b-a32c-4493-b9fc-90c8e9efebb2",
      "udi": "umb://element/69b59c793f2a45008dfabbfa7c4ea265",
      "negativePositive": "0",
      "lockInType": [
        "Economical"
      ],
      "bodyText": "<p>Offering a FiT above the average LCOE cost of solar, as determined by Lee et al. (2019) at 87.5 USD per MWh in 2018, motivated investors to explore low-hanging fruit in high-potential locations and locked in overpriced PPAs. In contrast to other countries, Viet Nam's FiT were fixed and not dynamically adjusted depending on demand and deployment.</p>"
    }
  ],
  "settingsData": []
}]]></Value>
