  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e64dc47-9486-4874-bae2-20baa89ebb6b",
      "udi": "umb://element/b6d33d5b801843b195e972292f3cbb05",
      "title": "Policy 1",
      "instrumentsText": "<p>Viet Nam's Renewable Energy Development Strategy to 2030, Vision to 2050 is cited as the first roadmap to emphasise the role of<br>renewable energy sources for reaching Viet Nam's economic and social development goals. It calls for encouraging investments in the development of renewables (Decision 2068/QD-TTg). </p>\n<p>Impact: Low <br>Impact indicator: To be added</p>",
      "policyDecision": [
        "Pro-active"
      ],
      "policyOrigin": [
        "Legislative"
      ],
      "typeOfPolicyInstrumentDropdown": [
        "Climate strategy"
      ],
      "jurisdiction": [
        "National"
      ],
      "enforcementLevel": [
        "Mandatory"
      ],
      "sectoralCoverage": [
        "Energy"
      ],
      "targetGroup": [
        "Policy makers"
      ],
      "institutionalRequirement": "",
      "implementationStatus": [
        "Fully implemented"
      ],
      "monitoringAndEvaluation": "",
      "startDateOfImplementation": "2015-11-25T00:00:00",
      "endDateOfImplementation": ""
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e64dc47-9486-4874-bae2-20baa89ebb6b",
      "udi": "umb://element/b83adb1180da45e89d803a9c86a2c351",
      "title": "Policy 2",
      "instrumentsText": "<p>Import tax exemptions for solar panels components (Decision 11/2017/QD-TTg).</p>\n<p>Impact: medium<br>Impact indicator: To be added</p>",
      "policyDecision": [
        "Supportive"
      ],
      "policyOrigin": [
        "Legislative"
      ],
      "typeOfPolicyInstrumentDropdown": [
        "Economic instruments - Fiscal incentives"
      ],
      "jurisdiction": [
        "National"
      ],
      "enforcementLevel": [
        "Mandatory"
      ],
      "sectoralCoverage": [
        "Energy"
      ],
      "targetGroup": [
        "Project developer"
      ],
      "institutionalRequirement": "",
      "implementationStatus": [
        "Fully implemented"
      ],
      "monitoringAndEvaluation": "",
      "startDateOfImplementation": "2017-06-01T00:00:00",
      "endDateOfImplementation": "2019-06-30T00:00:00"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e64dc47-9486-4874-bae2-20baa89ebb6b",
      "udi": "umb://element/653bf514ef614b8689b4c33ac0aac2ab",
      "title": "Policy 3",
      "instrumentsText": "<p>Corporate Tax: Solar developers receive a corporat income tax exemption for the first four years of operation, followed by a gradual reduction, with a 50% income tax reduction for the subsequent nine years and a 10% reduction annually until the 15th year (Decision 11/2017/QD-TTg)</p>\n<p>Impact: Medium<br>Impact indicator: To be added</p>",
      "policyDecision": [
        "Supportive"
      ],
      "policyOrigin": [
        "Legislative"
      ],
      "typeOfPolicyInstrumentDropdown": [
        "Economic instruments - Fiscal incentives"
      ],
      "jurisdiction": [
        "National"
      ],
      "enforcementLevel": [
        "Mandatory"
      ],
      "sectoralCoverage": [
        "Energy"
      ],
      "targetGroup": [
        "Project developer"
      ],
      "institutionalRequirement": "",
      "implementationStatus": [
        "Fully implemented"
      ],
      "monitoringAndEvaluation": "",
      "startDateOfImplementation": "2017-06-01T00:00:00",
      "endDateOfImplementation": "2019-06-30T00:00:00"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e64dc47-9486-4874-bae2-20baa89ebb6b",
      "udi": "umb://element/1910f9b1cdb144ec985fed345dd29655",
      "title": "Policy 4",
      "instrumentsText": "<p>Utility-scale solar projects are granted land lease payment exemptions, which can span from 3 years to the entire project's lifespan, depending on the project's location (Decision 11/2017/QD-TTg).</p>\n<p>Impact: Medium<br>Impact indicator: To be added</p>",
      "policyDecision": [
        "Supportive"
      ],
      "policyOrigin": [
        "Legislative"
      ],
      "typeOfPolicyInstrumentDropdown": [
        "Economic instruments - Fiscal incentives"
      ],
      "jurisdiction": [
        "National"
      ],
      "enforcementLevel": [
        "Mandatory"
      ],
      "sectoralCoverage": [
        "Energy"
      ],
      "targetGroup": [
        "Project developer"
      ],
      "institutionalRequirement": "",
      "implementationStatus": [
        "Fully implemented"
      ],
      "monitoringAndEvaluation": "",
      "startDateOfImplementation": "2017-06-01T00:00:00",
      "endDateOfImplementation": "2019-06-30T00:00:00"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e64dc47-9486-4874-bae2-20baa89ebb6b",
      "udi": "umb://element/7ab500dfedee4ddfb8cfe2e483612947",
      "title": "Policy 5",
      "instrumentsText": "<p>Feed-in tariffs 1: Electricity of Vietnam Corporation (EVN) buys all the output from solar cells with an efficiency above 16% deployed before 30/6/2019 at a set price of 93.5 USD per MWh for 20 years (Decision 11/2017/QD-TTg)</p>\n<p>Impact: High</p>\n<p>Impact indicator [Ex-post]: *Solar capacity increased from 0.01GW at the end of 2016 to 5.0 GW at the end of 2019.</p>\n<p>* Solar generation increased from 0.01 TWh in 2016 to 5.25 TWh in 2019</p>",
      "policyDecision": [
        "Pro-active"
      ],
      "policyOrigin": [
        "Legislative"
      ],
      "typeOfPolicyInstrumentDropdown": [
        "Economic instruments - Fiscal incentives"
      ],
      "jurisdiction": [
        "National"
      ],
      "enforcementLevel": [
        "Mandatory"
      ],
      "sectoralCoverage": [
        "Energy"
      ],
      "targetGroup": [
        "Project developer"
      ],
      "institutionalRequirement": "",
      "implementationStatus": [
        "Fully implemented"
      ],
      "monitoringAndEvaluation": "",
      "startDateOfImplementation": "2017-06-01T00:00:00",
      "endDateOfImplementation": "2019-06-30T00:00:00"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e64dc47-9486-4874-bae2-20baa89ebb6b",
      "udi": "umb://element/832904abe8ad4244872f060b87776e93",
      "title": "Policy 6",
      "instrumentsText": "<p>Two-way FiT System for rooftop solar (buying and selling from the grid), with the same purchasing price than the Fit1 (Decision 11/2017/QD-TTg)</p>\n<p>Impact: Medium<br>Impact indicator: To be added</p>",
      "policyDecision": [
        "Pro-active"
      ],
      "policyOrigin": [
        "Legislative"
      ],
      "typeOfPolicyInstrumentDropdown": [
        "Economic instruments - Fiscal incentives"
      ],
      "jurisdiction": [
        "National"
      ],
      "enforcementLevel": [
        "Mandatory"
      ],
      "sectoralCoverage": [
        "Energy"
      ],
      "targetGroup": [
        "Project developer"
      ],
      "institutionalRequirement": "",
      "implementationStatus": [
        "Fully implemented"
      ],
      "monitoringAndEvaluation": "",
      "startDateOfImplementation": "2017-06-01T00:00:00",
      "endDateOfImplementation": "2019-06-30T00:00:00"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e64dc47-9486-4874-bae2-20baa89ebb6b",
      "udi": "umb://element/5aea0ea72f4a4fa488dacf856964b44b",
      "title": "Policy 7",
      "instrumentsText": "<p>Feed-in tariffs 2: set at 76.8 USD per MWh for floating PVs, 70.9 USD per MWh for ground PVs and 83.8 USD for rooftop PVs, with PPAs of 20 years for projects starting operating before 31/12/2020 (Decision 13/2020/QD-TTg).</p>\n<p>Impact: High<br>Impact indicator [Ex-post]: * Solar capacity increased from 5.0 GW at the end of 2019 to 16.7 GW at the end of 2021.<br>* Solar generation increased from 5.25 TWh in 2019 to 25.8 TWh in 2021.</p>",
      "policyDecision": [
        "Pro-active"
      ],
      "policyOrigin": [
        "Legislative"
      ],
      "typeOfPolicyInstrumentDropdown": [
        "Economic instruments - Fiscal incentives"
      ],
      "jurisdiction": [
        "National"
      ],
      "enforcementLevel": [
        "Mandatory"
      ],
      "sectoralCoverage": [
        "Energy"
      ],
      "targetGroup": [
        "Project developer"
      ],
      "institutionalRequirement": "",
      "implementationStatus": [
        "Fully implemented"
      ],
      "monitoringAndEvaluation": "",
      "startDateOfImplementation": "2019-07-01T00:00:00",
      "endDateOfImplementation": "2020-12-31T00:00:00"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e64dc47-9486-4874-bae2-20baa89ebb6b",
      "udi": "umb://element/86e5c70e865d4339ab46d1ba26469259",
      "title": "Policy 8",
      "instrumentsText": "<p>The FiT price adjusment for the Ninh Tuan province: The FiT price point was set back at 93.5 USD per MWh for PV projects located in the Ninh Tuan province that did not meet the FiT1 deadline, until the regional 2 GW target is met (Decision No.115/NQ-CP)</p>\n<p><br>Impact: Medium<br>Impact indicator (Ex- post): * As of January 2021, the solar capacity installed in Ninh Thuan was 2.26 GW, well above the 2 GW objective.</p>",
      "policyDecision": [
        "Re-active"
      ],
      "policyOrigin": [
        "Legislative"
      ],
      "typeOfPolicyInstrumentDropdown": [
        "Economic instruments - Fiscal incentives"
      ],
      "jurisdiction": [
        "State/Region"
      ],
      "enforcementLevel": [
        "Mandatory"
      ],
      "sectoralCoverage": [
        "Energy"
      ],
      "targetGroup": [
        "Project developer"
      ],
      "institutionalRequirement": "",
      "implementationStatus": [
        "Fully implemented"
      ],
      "monitoringAndEvaluation": "",
      "startDateOfImplementation": "2018-08-31T00:00:00",
      "endDateOfImplementation": "2020-12-31T00:00:00"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "1e64dc47-9486-4874-bae2-20baa89ebb6b",
      "udi": "umb://element/03b4ec694ddf40fc8237961d3365fec5",
      "title": "Policy 9",
      "instrumentsText": "<p>Rooftop solar panels will use gross metering instead of net metering (Decision No. 02/2019/QD-TTg).</p>\n<p>Impact: Medium<br>Impact indicator: To be added</p>",
      "policyDecision": [
        "Re-active"
      ],
      "policyOrigin": [
        "Legislative"
      ],
      "typeOfPolicyInstrumentDropdown": [
        "Regulatory instruments - Others"
      ],
      "jurisdiction": [
        "National"
